<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2030&amp;p=10203#p10203</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2030&amp;p=10203#p10203"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Experiment # 5 Out There.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2030&amp;p=10203#p10203"><![CDATA[
Experiment # 5 Out There.<br />Major changes made from Smoked Glass skin. <br /><br />Misty here, <br />clear out there.<br /><br />Yep. One of those iconic beach views.<br />Fake of course, almost like a cartoon.<br />The horizon will wander up and down somewhat. Not sure if anything can be done about that?<br />I still find it amazing that all these menus, <br />make most of themselves, using very efficient way of stretching! <br /><br />Tried with CSM 4.0.2 on Win7/8. Autocolor background glass select, only works on Win8. <br />If required, change static color, in &quot;personalize&quot; feature, of Win7 .<br />Not compatible with most older versions of CSM. Will only partially work.<br />After downloading file, paste in skins folder. Exit CSM, restart CSM, <br />and go to &quot;Start Menu Style&quot; tab. Pick Classic or Classic two columns.<br />Pick &quot;Out There&quot; in Skin tab. <br /><br />ps. Feel free to change anything in this skin, especially my errors, <br />as it's just an experiment. I'm no artist or coder, just playing around with stuff.<br />Sometimes errors can lead to new ideas. <br />In this case, the vertical noise problem in the making of a previous skin, <br />gave me the idea for using it here.<br />So, there is a lot of streaking of carefully selected one pixel wide noise, <br />mostly for the fake waves.<br />Nothing is permanent, everything changes.<br />You could make it better. French doors, light to dark sand, sunset, moon glow, etc. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />Just noticed 4.0.4 is out, Hopefully still works.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sun Jan 19, 2014 8:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
